WEBVTT

00:10.552 --> 00:11.720
♪ You could do it solo ♪

00:11.720 --> 00:13.722
♪ But then you'd be
All by yourself ♪

00:13.722 --> 00:16.225
♪ Yo! So it'd be more fun
To share this one ♪

00:16.225 --> 00:17.726
♪ With someone else ♪

00:17.726 --> 00:21.647
♪ Together we will soar
Across the sky and beyond ♪

00:21.647 --> 00:22.773
♪ So turn up your voice ♪

00:23.690 --> 00:25.567
♪ Stand up and sing along! ♪

00:25.567 --> 00:26.777
♪ All different voices ♪

00:26.777 --> 00:27.778
♪ Everybody now! ♪

00:27.778 --> 00:29.154
♪ Our melodies ringing ♪

00:29.154 --> 00:31.031
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:31.031 --> 00:33.158
♪ Yeah
We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:33.158 --> 00:36.787
♪ Our song is much stronger
With every Troll singing ♪

00:36.787 --> 00:39.414
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪♪

00:40.832 --> 00:42.793
♪

00:43.335 --> 00:46.838
[ Poppy humming ]

00:46.922 --> 00:48.090
HOLLY:
Poppy! Poppy!

00:48.173 --> 00:50.092
Oh! I have I got something to show you!

00:50.509 --> 00:53.303
But I gotta warn you, it's really cute.

00:54.805 --> 00:57.432
‐ Holly, please, I adore cute.

00:57.683 --> 00:59.268
I hardly think I need a warn‐‐

00:59.351 --> 01:00.269
[ gasp ]

01:00.519 --> 01:01.353
[ squeak ]

01:03.397 --> 01:04.564
HOLLY:
Poppy.

01:04.564 --> 01:06.024
Poppy, you okay, girl?

01:06.441 --> 01:08.527
‐ Holly, who is that?

01:08.527 --> 01:09.611
[ giggle ]

01:09.611 --> 01:10.862
‐ That's Pigtail!

01:11.613 --> 01:14.074
See, now that I'm settled
here in TrollsTopia,

01:14.324 --> 01:17.786
I figured it was time
to send home for my BPF.

01:20.455 --> 01:21.832
‐ Sorry, "BPF"?

01:22.416 --> 01:23.417
[ Pigtail growls ]

01:23.417 --> 01:25.752
‐ Uh, Best Pet Friend?

01:26.336 --> 01:28.714
Surely you have pets
in the Pop Tribe, right?

01:28.880 --> 01:30.591
I mean, what about...?

01:31.466 --> 01:34.720
‐ What? Mr. Dinkles is not a pet.

01:35.679 --> 01:38.599
[ laughing ]

01:40.809 --> 01:44.062
‐ Uh, I guess I stand corrected?

01:44.313 --> 01:46.523
‐ Yeah, BPF's must be one of those things

01:46.523 --> 01:48.734
that's unique
to the Country Western Tribe.

01:49.151 --> 01:50.569
‐ Oh, really?

01:50.569 --> 01:53.488
♪

01:53.572 --> 01:54.531
[ squeal ]

01:54.614 --> 01:56.950
[ chirping ]

01:57.367 --> 01:59.411
‐ Eh!

02:02.956 --> 02:03.874
[ squeal ]

02:04.541 --> 02:06.877
‐ You, you all have BPF's?

02:07.044 --> 02:08.003
‐ Well, yeah.

02:08.170 --> 02:10.839
When I heard Holly's pet
was coming to TrollsTopia...

02:10.839 --> 02:13.842
I decided to send home
for old Fang here...

02:14.176 --> 02:16.011
Didn't I, my wittle boy?

02:16.511 --> 02:20.182
‐ Uh, Val, I think your "wittle boy"

02:20.182 --> 02:22.517
is trying to squeeze
all the air out your lungs.

02:22.976 --> 02:23.810
‐ Oh, yeah.

02:24.770 --> 02:26.813
We call those his "love hugs."

02:27.022 --> 02:29.232
Yes, we do, yes, we do!

02:29.441 --> 02:30.275
Ah!

02:31.151 --> 02:32.194
Aww!

02:32.444 --> 02:35.322
‐ Okay, I've seen enough,
I have to have a BPF.

02:35.697 --> 02:37.407
But how do I find one?

02:37.616 --> 02:40.077
‐ Oh, we can help with that, sugar.

02:40.285 --> 02:43.372
There's tons of critters
looking for a Troll to care for them.

02:44.164 --> 02:47.709
‐ Yeah, like I always say,
"There's plenty of birds in the sea!"

02:47.709 --> 02:48.627
[ squeal ]

02:50.545 --> 02:54.341
‐ All right, Poppy,
we've found a great critter match for you.

02:54.633 --> 02:58.136
She's got a big personality
and an even bigger heart.

02:58.512 --> 03:01.431
Say hello to Perky, the grin‐chilla!

03:01.431 --> 03:03.475
♪

03:03.475 --> 03:04.518
[ squeak ]

03:05.352 --> 03:07.020
‐ Aww!

03:09.272 --> 03:10.107
[ gasp ]

03:10.440 --> 03:11.483
Hmm!

03:12.734 --> 03:14.027
‐ Yeah, I'd pet that.

03:16.738 --> 03:18.990
[ Poppy laughs ]

03:19.449 --> 03:23.120
‐ Oh, that's funny, you are funny.

03:23.412 --> 03:26.123
Did you hear the one about
the glitter covered almonds?

03:26.331 --> 03:28.208
They're pretty nuts!

03:28.458 --> 03:29.543
[ squeaking ]

03:29.543 --> 03:32.838
[ laughing ]

03:33.296 --> 03:34.131
[ sigh ]

03:35.674 --> 03:39.886
You know, they say when you can share
a comfortable silence with someone,

03:39.886 --> 03:41.847
it's a sign of compatibility.

03:42.305 --> 03:45.934
Or maybe I could say, "competibility..."

03:48.562 --> 03:52.482
Anyway, I'll get some refreshments,
make yourself at home.

03:52.816 --> 03:56.069
[ Perky squeaks ]

03:58.697 --> 04:02.951
So, Perky? Today has been just so great.

04:02.951 --> 04:04.828
And I know it's really soon,

04:04.828 --> 04:08.582
but what would you say
if I asked you to be my BP‐‐?

04:11.126 --> 04:13.211
[ growling ]

04:13.211 --> 04:14.087
[ gasp ]

04:15.672 --> 04:17.382
It was a BPF...

04:17.841 --> 04:18.717
disaster.

04:18.842 --> 04:20.886
‐ Oh, sorry, girlfriend.

04:21.303 --> 04:23.054
‐ Yeah. You wanna hold Fang?

04:23.054 --> 04:24.347
[ hissing ]

04:24.347 --> 04:25.724
Might make you feel better?

04:26.975 --> 04:28.643
‐ Uh... I'm good.

04:28.852 --> 04:32.147
‐ Okay, so Perky didn't work out, so what?

04:32.355 --> 04:35.025
Poppy, you don't stop
swinging at the pinata

04:35.025 --> 04:37.694
just cause' the candy
didn't drop on the first whack.

04:37.861 --> 04:40.113
‐ I find this metaphor relatable.

04:40.113 --> 04:43.658
‐ Then let's go get you
another critter to call BPF!

04:43.867 --> 04:45.243
Go team?

04:45.619 --> 04:46.912
‐ Go team!

04:47.204 --> 04:48.371
VAL:
Go team!

04:50.123 --> 04:53.585
‐ It's such a pleasure to meet you.
Tell me all about yourself.

04:53.919 --> 04:56.922
‐ Brack! A hug is a sign
of emotional weakness

04:56.922 --> 05:00.133
and is inferior
to a firm handshake. Brack!

05:01.802 --> 05:03.845
‐ Okay, this has been great.

05:05.013 --> 05:08.517
So, you're nocturnal!
What's it like staying up all night?

05:08.517 --> 05:11.394
[ snoring ]

05:11.394 --> 05:12.229
Ugh.

05:13.313 --> 05:15.357
♪

05:15.357 --> 05:17.984
I gotta say, I've had a really good time.

05:18.401 --> 05:20.695
Maybe you and I
could take this to the next‐‐

05:20.695 --> 05:24.950
[ ducks quacking ]

05:24.950 --> 05:25.867
[ quack ]

05:26.660 --> 05:28.328
Oh. I see.

05:28.328 --> 05:29.454
[ quack ]

05:29.454 --> 05:30.288
Of course.

05:30.497 --> 05:34.000
If you have to go south for the winter,
I understand.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.711
♪

05:36.711 --> 05:37.796
[ quack ]

05:37.796 --> 05:40.173
[ ducks quacking ]

05:40.173 --> 05:41.800
I'll never forget you either.

05:42.676 --> 05:44.803
Ugh! I give up.

05:45.178 --> 05:47.889
‐ Oh, now don't lose hope, Poppy girl.

05:48.098 --> 05:52.143
You know, sometimes you find a BPF
when you least expect it.

05:52.352 --> 05:54.521
‐ Oh, come on. Let's be real, guys,

05:54.604 --> 05:58.400
my BPF isn't just gonna pop up outta no‐‐
Whoa, whoa!

06:02.112 --> 06:03.029
[ squeak ]

06:07.534 --> 06:10.412
Well, hello there, Mr. Turtle.

06:10.412 --> 06:11.288
[ squeak ]

06:11.746 --> 06:14.499
Oh, Mr. Turtle was your father's name?

06:14.499 --> 06:15.333
[ giggle ]

06:15.709 --> 06:19.129
Okay then, yes, I will call you Shelliot.

06:19.754 --> 06:21.256
That's really cute by the way.

06:21.965 --> 06:22.799
[ gasp ]

06:22.799 --> 06:24.593
‐ Yeah! Woo‐hoo!
‐ Yeah!

06:25.176 --> 06:28.430
‐ So, um, are you busy today?

06:28.722 --> 06:30.807
Wanna go play fetch?

06:30.807 --> 06:31.808
[ squeak ]

06:32.767 --> 06:36.938
What? No, bleh, what am I saying?
Turtles don't play fetch.

06:37.647 --> 06:38.481
[ giggle ]

06:38.481 --> 06:41.192
Oh, I'm sorry,
I'm just really nervous and‐‐

06:41.192 --> 06:42.027
Oh!

06:42.027 --> 06:43.612
[ squeaking ]

06:43.612 --> 06:46.323
Oh, you're going to make the plans?

06:46.323 --> 06:50.201
Wow, I guess you could say
you swept me off my feet.

06:50.201 --> 06:52.537
[ giggle ]

06:53.747 --> 06:54.748
[ squealing ]

06:55.582 --> 07:00.086
♪ I get the feeling
When I'm here with you ♪

07:00.503 --> 07:04.758
♪ There's nothing wrong in the world ♪

07:04.758 --> 07:06.676
♪ So get closer ♪

07:06.676 --> 07:07.969
♪ Get closer ♪

07:07.969 --> 07:10.513
♪ Get closer ♪

07:10.513 --> 07:14.768
♪ Let me hold you
Let me look in your eyes ♪

07:15.477 --> 07:17.437
♪ When you know it ♪

07:17.437 --> 07:18.438
♪ You know it ♪

07:18.438 --> 07:21.149
♪ You know it ♪

07:21.149 --> 07:25.487
♪ You're everything I need in my life ♪

07:25.945 --> 07:30.283
♪ In my life ♪♪

07:30.283 --> 07:34.996
‐ Oh! It sounds like things with Shelliot
are going very well.

07:34.996 --> 07:36.790
Do I hear collar bells?

07:36.790 --> 07:38.166
[ bell rings ]

07:38.166 --> 07:39.834
‐ Oh! I think so!

07:40.251 --> 07:43.630
In fact, I'm on my way to meet him
for cupcakes now and...

07:44.130 --> 07:46.132
I personalized his bowl.

07:46.132 --> 07:47.676
HOLLY: Oh!
VAL: Oh!

07:47.842 --> 07:51.638
‐ And you know, I'm glad I struck it out
with all those other pets,

07:51.930 --> 07:56.935
cause' now I see what Shelliot and I have
is really special.

07:56.935 --> 07:58.353
[ Shelliot squeaks ]

07:58.353 --> 08:00.355
Oh, there he is now!

08:00.355 --> 08:01.731
‐ Good luck, Poppy girl!

08:02.023 --> 08:02.857
[ sigh ]

08:03.858 --> 08:05.151
[ Branch giggles ]

08:05.151 --> 08:06.069
[ gasp ]

08:06.277 --> 08:07.779
‐ Come on, boy! Fetch!

08:07.779 --> 08:10.198
[ laughing in slow motion ]

08:21.876 --> 08:24.295
[ laughing ]

08:25.338 --> 08:26.172
‐ No!

08:27.507 --> 08:28.341
‐ Poppy?

08:28.341 --> 08:30.343
[ squeaking ]

08:30.719 --> 08:34.264
‐ Oh, I think this is exactly
what it looks like, Shelliot.

08:34.264 --> 08:35.390
[ squeaking ]

08:35.390 --> 08:38.518
Or should I go back
to calling you Mr. Turtle?

08:39.686 --> 08:42.480
‐ Uh, is something wrong?

08:42.689 --> 08:44.691
‐ Yeah, it is, Branch.

08:44.858 --> 08:48.653
Turtles don't play fetch,
or so I was led to believe.

08:48.653 --> 08:49.571
[ squeak ]

08:50.238 --> 08:51.281
‐ Oh, right.

08:51.281 --> 08:52.240
[ giggle ]

08:52.240 --> 08:54.117
I guess it is kinda odd, huh?

08:54.617 --> 08:58.705
But I came across Shelliot here
and it just felt right.

08:59.122 --> 09:00.498
We just seem to have this...

09:00.832 --> 09:02.083
connection, you know?

09:02.500 --> 09:04.461
‐ Yeah, I do know, Branch.

09:04.753 --> 09:08.673
Cause' Shelliot and I have just as much
of a connection, if not more so.

09:08.882 --> 09:10.216
See? Come on, boy!

09:10.216 --> 09:12.135
Come on! Fetch!

09:12.969 --> 09:13.803
[ scream ]

09:18.099 --> 09:18.933
[ clears throat ]

09:18.933 --> 09:21.686
Well, it seems I've made a mistake.

09:22.103 --> 09:23.730
Shelliot, you and Branch

09:23.730 --> 09:26.316
clearly have something we don't,
which is great.

09:26.691 --> 09:29.694
Frankly, I wasn't sure
we were a good fit anyway.

09:33.823 --> 09:34.866
Oh, that?

09:35.492 --> 09:36.326
That was just‐‐

09:37.118 --> 09:38.078
I've gotta go!

09:38.078 --> 09:40.914
[ Poppy crying ]

09:43.792 --> 09:45.251
‐ There, there, sugar.

09:46.002 --> 09:47.003
‐ That's rough.

09:47.295 --> 09:50.548
‐ It's just,
with every pet that gets away,

09:50.882 --> 09:54.552
it feels like I'm just gonna
wind up alone, you know?

09:54.552 --> 09:57.847
Like I'm destined to be
one of those old cat ladies...

09:58.556 --> 10:00.809
but with no cats.

10:01.851 --> 10:04.104
‐ Poppy, no, don't say that!

10:04.395 --> 10:06.064
‐ Yeah, that's not gonna happen.

10:06.064 --> 10:08.733
‐ Then how come it never works out?

10:09.359 --> 10:10.568
Even with Perky.

10:10.777 --> 10:14.114
I mean, she seemed like the perfect BPF

10:14.114 --> 10:17.450
and then she tore up
one of my scrapbooks.

10:18.785 --> 10:20.829
‐ Wait, she ate your scrapbook?

10:21.121 --> 10:22.372
You never told us that.

10:22.747 --> 10:25.208
‐ You said, "It was a BPF disaster."

10:26.042 --> 10:28.128
‐ Well yeah, it was.

10:28.670 --> 10:29.504
Wasn't it?

10:30.421 --> 10:33.007
[ laughing ]

10:33.007 --> 10:35.718
‐ Are you kidding? That's nothing!

10:35.718 --> 10:39.180
Do you have any idea
how often Pigtail ruins my stuff?

10:39.180 --> 10:40.390
[ growl ]

10:40.932 --> 10:41.808
‐ For real!

10:42.100 --> 10:44.936
Sometimes I get a feeling
that Fang just wants to eat me.

10:47.605 --> 10:51.526
‐ Poppy, there is no such thing
as a perfect BPF.

10:51.985 --> 10:55.738
The question is,
are you perfect for each other?

11:01.452 --> 11:06.040
♪ I get the feeling
When I'm here with you ♪

11:06.583 --> 11:11.004
♪ There's nothing wrong in the world ♪

11:11.004 --> 11:12.714
♪ So get closer ♪

11:12.714 --> 11:13.840
♪ Get closer ♪

11:13.840 --> 11:16.551
♪ Get closer ♪

11:16.551 --> 11:18.928
♪ Let me hold you
Let me look in your eyes ♪

11:18.928 --> 11:20.221
‐ Oh, Perky!

11:21.389 --> 11:23.349
♪ When you know it ♪

11:23.349 --> 11:24.642
♪ You know it ♪

11:24.642 --> 11:26.936
♪ You know it ♪

11:26.936 --> 11:28.271
♪ You're everything... ♪

11:28.271 --> 11:32.483
‐ Aww, now, ain't that just
the sweetest thing you've ever seen, Val?

11:32.483 --> 11:33.526
♪ In my life ♪♪

11:33.526 --> 11:34.402
‐ Val?

11:35.069 --> 11:37.113
VAL:
Yeah... It's very sweet.

11:39.991 --> 11:41.993
♪

11:45.205 --> 11:47.624
‐ Next patient for examination is...

11:48.041 --> 11:51.211
Valentina Danger‐Skull Thundershock?

11:51.836 --> 11:53.296
‐ Valentina?
‐ Valentina?

11:53.296 --> 11:55.715
‐ Ha, my full name rocks so hard.

11:56.174 --> 11:58.801
Yeah!

11:59.510 --> 12:03.473
‐ Gotta hand it to you, Poppy girl,
it was a great idea to suggest

12:03.473 --> 12:05.808
every Troll get a follicle fitness test.

12:06.142 --> 12:08.519
‐ Thanks, Holly.
Nothing's more important to me

12:08.519 --> 12:11.231
than making sure TrollsTopia
is hair healthy.

12:11.940 --> 12:13.066
‐ Stick out your bangs.

12:13.399 --> 12:14.567
‐ Ah!

12:15.151 --> 12:17.111
‐ Someone's been brushing.

12:18.863 --> 12:21.783
♪

12:22.617 --> 12:23.868
Nothing unusual here.

12:24.744 --> 12:25.828
Want to know a secret?

12:26.162 --> 12:28.831
Doctors only do this test
because it's fun.

12:29.958 --> 12:35.546
[ humming a can‐can song ]

12:36.256 --> 12:37.674
Holly Darlin'?

12:38.007 --> 12:41.344
‐ Good luck, Holly!
‐ Oh, Poppy, trust me.

12:41.636 --> 12:45.431
With hair this tall and gorgeous,
I can't fail.

12:46.349 --> 12:48.726
I failed? But...

12:49.018 --> 12:52.522
my hair, it's so tall and gorgeous.

12:52.522 --> 12:55.817
Agreed.
But volume and hold on this scale

12:55.817 --> 12:58.361
requires a large amount of hair products,

12:58.361 --> 13:03.533
which, when taken in excess,
lead to poor hair health.

13:04.325 --> 13:08.204
‐ Oh, but I don't use a lotta hairspray.

13:09.330 --> 13:10.164
Oops.

13:10.164 --> 13:11.082
[ giggle ]

13:11.082 --> 13:12.667
Now how did that get in there?

13:14.877 --> 13:17.463
Okay! So I use a lotta hairspray!

13:18.756 --> 13:21.426
It's just the way it's always been.

13:22.427 --> 13:25.388
Every week,
when I was just a li'l Country Troll,

13:25.388 --> 13:27.348
my mama would treat me and my 'do

13:27.348 --> 13:30.560
to H. T. Hairnum's wagon
of Hair Care Wares.

13:31.102 --> 13:34.147
‐ I'm sorry, who is H. T. Hairnum?

13:34.147 --> 13:35.273
[ eagle screeches ]

13:35.273 --> 13:37.483
‐ Who is H. T. Hairnum?

13:37.483 --> 13:38.401
[ whip snaps ]

13:38.401 --> 13:43.406
‐ Only the purveyor of the most decadent
hair delights in all of Lonesome Flats.

13:43.990 --> 13:47.994
Why, rubbin' in just a dab of his pomade

13:47.994 --> 13:52.040
is like giving your hair a great big hug.

13:53.207 --> 13:54.417
Well, goodbye.

13:54.417 --> 13:55.835
[ eagle screeches ]

13:56.335 --> 13:58.713
‐ How is that bird getting in here?

13:59.297 --> 14:03.009
Holly, I want you to give up hairspray
for six weeks.

14:03.009 --> 14:03.926
[ gasp ]

14:03.926 --> 14:06.679
‐ No! She didn't mean it, beautiful.

14:07.930 --> 14:09.182
‐ Yes, I did.

14:09.557 --> 14:12.185
At that time,
you'll retake the fitness test.

14:12.560 --> 14:15.313
Meanwhile, I'm prescribing this.

14:17.023 --> 14:19.067
‐ "One membership to..."?

14:19.358 --> 14:21.152
‐ The Hairnasium!

14:21.152 --> 14:24.405
♪

14:24.405 --> 14:26.657
‐ Oh, Poppy, I don't know.

14:26.949 --> 14:29.702
No hairspray, exhausting exercise.

14:30.328 --> 14:33.081
I'm not sure
I'm cut out to be hair healthy.

14:33.081 --> 14:34.957
‐ Of course you are, Holly.

14:34.957 --> 14:37.835
Especially with Synth and Smidge
as your trainers.

14:38.169 --> 14:39.879
‐ Woo‐hoo!
‐ Woo‐hoo!

14:39.879 --> 14:43.341
‐ Yo, Holly, we're ready to do this!
Are you ready to do this?

14:44.217 --> 14:46.010
‐ I... guess so?

14:46.177 --> 14:48.805
‐ She guesses so!

14:48.805 --> 14:50.515
‐ Yeah!
‐ Yeah!

14:50.515 --> 14:52.850
‐ Just so you know,
when it comes to helping you

14:52.850 --> 14:55.103
get your hair healthy, we give 100%!

14:55.103 --> 14:58.022
‐ Then we add 12 to that!
‐ Then we double that!

14:58.022 --> 14:59.190
‐ Then we take a second,

14:59.190 --> 15:02.068
cause' the math got pretty complicated.
And we get...

15:02.401 --> 15:04.195
‐ 224%!
‐ 224%!

15:04.195 --> 15:06.114
‐ 224?
‐ 224!

15:06.114 --> 15:08.157
‐ 224?
‐ 224!

15:08.449 --> 15:10.118
‐ Yeah!
‐ Yeah!

15:10.118 --> 15:12.745
[ cheering ]

15:13.287 --> 15:16.541
‐ Now, don't worry, the Hairnasium's
got something for everyone.

15:16.666 --> 15:17.959
Like hair‐robics.

15:18.417 --> 15:20.128
‐ Oh. Woah! Ah.

15:20.128 --> 15:21.671
SYNTH:
<i>Spin classes.</i>

15:21.879 --> 15:23.256
‐ Come on, everybody!

15:24.006 --> 15:26.175
Keep spinning those records!

15:26.175 --> 15:27.677
Hey, oh!

15:27.927 --> 15:31.139
SMIDGE: <i>And even</i>
<i>an all‐organic hair nutrition cafe.</i>

15:31.597 --> 15:32.557
‐ Ah!

15:34.142 --> 15:36.102
‐ And the results speak for themselves.

15:36.769 --> 15:38.479
When Minuet first came to us,

15:38.479 --> 15:41.149
her hair could barely lift
an ice cream sprinkle.

15:41.149 --> 15:42.859
But look at her now!

15:43.276 --> 15:44.402
‐ Ah!

15:44.402 --> 15:46.237
[ Trolls cheering ]

15:46.237 --> 15:47.446
‐ You got this!

15:47.446 --> 15:48.990
